    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gundersen Acquires British Company</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By STUART ELLIOT</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gundersen Partners LLC, which specializes in executive searches for marketing, advertising and communications companies, has acquired Bucher/Rugman in London, which has similar specialties; financial terms undisclosed (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Gundersen Partners L.L.C. in New York, which specializes in executive searches for marketing, advertising and communications companies, has acquired Bucher/Rugman in London, which has similar specialties. Terms were not disclosed.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Gundersen Partners L.L.C. in New York, which specializes in executive searches for marketing, advertising and communications companies, has acquired Bucher/Rugman in London, which has similar specialties. Terms were not disclosed.</p>
        <p>Bucher/Rugman will be merged with Gundersen to form a new London office for Gundersen under the name Gundersen Bucher Rugman. Tony Bucher and Nigel Rugman will remain joint managing directors.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
